reviews.body:
So to summarize, a new flow is as follows:

# collect counters
1. lock;
2. make local copies of OIDs;
3. unlock;
4. read counters from SAI
5. write to DB;
# run plugins
6. lock;
7. make local copies of OIDs;
8. unlock;
9. run plugins on local copies of OIDs;

If between step 3 and 6 new OID will be registered, its counters won't be written to DB but the plugin will run for this OID. It's not a big issue since syncd won't crash.

Also, local copies of plugins' SHA vectors need to be created under lock in runPlugins and not only local copies of OIDs.
